text:
Hello Everybody.  Question:  I download latest fabric from gerrit and intend to make a peer image from scratch as following:
#cd fabric
# make peer
Then it gives me a error:

-cp build/docker/gotools/bin/protoc-gen-go build/bin/chaintool build/goshim.tar.bz2 build/image/ccenv/payload
-cp: cannot stat 'build/docker/gotools/bin/protoc-gen-go': No such file or directory

I find that protoc-gen-go   exist  in  build/gotools/bin instead of build/docker/gotools/bin.
So I copied protoc-gen-go to  build/docker/gotools/bin, it passed.

I wonder if it is a bug?
